<font face="Comic Sans MS">Steady on, mate.
Where you going?</font>

774
01:33:43,680 --> 01:33:44,680
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Move!</font>

775
01:33:48,960 --> 01:33:50,030
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Let me by!</font>

776
01:33:54,560 --> 01:33:55,710
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Let me through!</font>

777
01:33:55,800 --> 01:33:59,077
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Remember, follow your platoon commander.</font>

778
01:33:59,800 --> 01:34:02,793
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Stay spread out
and watch for his orders.</font>

779
01:34:02,880 --> 01:34:05,873
<font face="Comic Sans MS">- Where is your commanding officer?
- He's in the holding pen.</font>

780
01:34:05,960 --> 01:34:09,840
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Raise your signal flags
or fire the signal flares</font>

781
01:34:09,920 --> 01:34:12,480
<font face="Comic Sans MS">when you've taken your section
of the Hun line.</font>

782
01:34:12,560 --> 01:34:15,519
<font face="Comic Sans MS">B Company, stand to.
Now listen and listen well.</font>

783
01:34:15,600 --> 01:34:17,592
<font face="Comic Sans MS">On the first mark,
A Company will advance.</font>

784
01:34:17,680 --> 01:34:19,831
<font face="Comic Sans MS">B Company will then move
to the front line.</font>

785
01:34:19,920 --> 01:34:22,116
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Sir. I have a message
from General Erinmore.</font>

786
01:34:22,200 --> 01:34:24,635
<font face="Comic Sans MS">- Who the fuck are you?
- The attack has been called off.</font>

787
01:34:24,760 --> 01:34:26,592
<font face="Comic Sans MS">General Erinmore
has called off the attack.</font>

788
01:34:26,720 --> 01:34:29,713
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Balls, man. We're about to go over.
We've got them on the run!</font>

789
01:34:29,800 --> 01:34:31,553
<font face="Comic Sans MS">You don't.
Please don't send your men over.</font>

790
01:34:31,640 --> 01:34:32,640
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Get out of the way!</font>

791
01:34:32,680 --> 01:34:35,718
<font face="Comic Sans MS">These are direct orders from army command!
Where is Colonel Mackenzie?</font>

792
01:34:35,800 --> 01:34:38,520
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Jesus Christ, man!
Go and see the captain!</font>

793
01:34:38,600 --> 01:34:40,881
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Now, I want us up there quickly,
you understand?</font>

794
01:34:40,920 --> 01:34:43,560
<font face="Comic Sans MS">- Do you understand?
- Yes, sir!</font>

795
01:34:44,680 --> 01:34:47,400
<font face="Comic Sans MS">NCOs collect flares and signal flags.
Keep to your stations.</font>

796
01:34:47,480 --> 01:34:48,880
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Oi. Oi!</font>

797
01:34:57,400 --> 01:34:59,960
<font face="Comic Sans MS">9 and 10 section at the ready!</font>

798
01:35:00,680 --> 01:35:03,957
<font face="Comic Sans MS">We will advance
on the first whistle blast!</font>

799
01:35:06,320 --> 01:35:08,516
<font face="Comic Sans MS">The man next to you falls, keep moving.</font>

800
01:35:08,640 --> 01:35:10,791
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Your orders are to break the lines.</font>

801
01:35:10,880 --> 01:35:13,190
<font face="Comic Sans MS">- Where is the captain?
- He's over there.</font>

802
01:35:15,600 --> 01:35:17,592
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Sir! Sir!</font>

803
01:35:19,080 --> 01:35:21,356
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Captain, I have a message.</font>

804
01:35:21,440 --> 01:35:22,840
<font face="Comic Sans MS">This attack is called off.</font>

805
01:35:22,920 --> 01:35:25,276
<font face="Comic Sans MS">You have to stop.
You have to stop.</font>

806
01:35:29,200 --> 01:35:30,634
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Where is Colonel Mackenzie?</font>

807
01:35:31,280 --> 01:35:33,431
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Where is Mackenzie?</font>

808
01:36:03,360 --> 01:36:05,477
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Back! Hold fast!</font>

809
01:36:07,920 --> 01:36:11,072
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Sir, I have orders to stop this attack!</font>

810
01:36:11,200 --> 01:36:12,200
<font face="Comic Sans MS">What?</font>

811
01:36:12,280 --> 01:36:14,590
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Where is Colonel Mackenzie?</font>

812
01:36:14,680 --> 01:36:16,399
<font face="Comic Sans MS">He's further up the line.</font>

813
01:36:16,480 --> 01:36:17,480
<font face="Comic Sans MS">How far?</font>

814
01:36:17,481 --> 01:36:20,041
<font face="Comic Sans MS">300 yards.
He's in a cut-and-cover.</font>

815
01:36:20,120 --> 01:36:22,794
<font face="Comic Sans MS">You'll have to wait
until the first wave goes over.</font>

816
01:36:22,920 --> 01:36:24,877
<font face="Comic Sans MS">No. No, I can't.</font>

817
01:36:32,640 --> 01:36:36,031
<font face="Comic Sans MS">7 platoon,
30 seconds!</font>

818
01:36:47,760 --> 01:36:51,037
<font face="Comic Sans MS">You can't possibly make it that way, man!
Are you bloody insane?</font>

819
01:36:55,680 --> 01:36:57,831
<font face="Comic Sans MS">What the hell are you doing,
Lance Corporal?</font>

820
01:36:58,320 --> 01:37:00,073
<font face="Comic Sans MS">No! No, no, no, no!</font>

821
01:38:04,880 --> 01:38:06,394
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Get ready!</font>

822
01:38:06,480 --> 01:38:08,631
<font face="Comic Sans MS">- Colonel Mackenzie!
- He's in there.</font>

823
01:38:10,400 --> 01:38:11,470
<font face="Comic Sans MS">2 minutes!</font>

824
01:38:11,960 --> 01:38:12,960
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Let me through!</font>

825
01:38:13,040 --> 01:38:14,713
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Hey! Hey!</font>

826
01:38:14,800 --> 01:38:17,634
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Let me through! I have to get through!</font>

827
01:38:17,720 --> 01:38:18,976
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I have to see Colonel Mackenzie!</font>

828
01:38:19,000 --> 01:38:20,736
<font face="Comic Sans MS">- What are you doing?
- I have to stop this attack!</font>

829
01:38:20,760 --> 01:38:21,910
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Colonel, we've seen flares.</font>

830
01:38:22,040 --> 01:38:24,160
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Men on the left flank
have made it to the German line.</font>

831
01:38:24,240 --> 01:38:26,516
<font face="Comic Sans MS">- Colonel! Colonel!
- Hold him! Hold him!</font>

832
01:38:26,600 --> 01:38:28,876
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Listen to me.
Listen to me. I have a letter.</font>

833
01:38:28,960 --> 01:38:30,519
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I need to see Colonel Mackenzie.</font>

834
01:38:30,600 --> 01:38:32,296
<font face="Comic Sans MS">There's no bloody way
you're gettin' in there!</font>

835
01:38:32,320 --> 01:38:33,959
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Sergeant, send the next wave!</font>

836
01:38:34,040 --> 01:38:35,156
<font face="Comic Sans MS">No!</font>

837
01:38:35,240 --> 01:38:37,277
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Second wave,
prepare yourselves!</font>

838
01:38:37,360 --> 01:38:39,336
<font face="Comic Sans MS">- Colonel Mackenzie!
- Concentrate everything there.</font>

839
01:38:39,360 --> 01:38:41,636
<font face="Comic Sans MS">This attack is not to go ahead!</font>

840
01:38:41,720 --> 01:38:44,394
<font face="Comic Sans MS">You have been ordered to stop!
You have to stop!</font>

841
01:38:44,520 --> 01:38:45,840
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Who the hell are you?</font>

842
01:38:46,360 --> 01:38:48,716
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Lance Corporal Schofield, sir, 8th.</font>

843
01:38:48,800 --> 01:38:51,554
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I have orders from General Erinmore
to call off this attack.</font>

844
01:38:51,640 --> 01:38:53,040
<font face="Comic Sans MS">You're too late, Lance Corporal.</font>

845
01:38:53,120 --> 01:38:56,636
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Sir, these orders are from army command.
You have to read them.</font>

846
01:38:56,720 --> 01:38:59,776
<font face="Comic Sans MS">- Shall we hold back the second wave, sir?
- No, Major. Hesitate now and we lose.</font>

847
01:38:59,800 --> 01:39:02,031
<font face="Comic Sans MS">- Victory's only 500 yards away.
- Sir!</font>

848
01:39:02,120 --> 01:39:03,270
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Please, read the letter.</font>

849
01:39:03,360 --> 01:39:06,319
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I have heard it all before.</font>

850
01:39:06,400 --> 01:39:08,471
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I'm not gonna wait until dusk or for fog.</font>

851
01:39:08,560 --> 01:39:11,360
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I'm not calling back my men only
to send them out there again tomorrow,</font>

852
01:39:11,400 --> 01:39:12,976
<font face="Comic Sans MS">not when we've got the bastards
on the run.</font>

853
01:39:13,000 --> 01:39:15,595
<font face="Comic Sans MS">- This is their last stand.
- The Germans planned this, sir.</font>

854
01:39:17,040 --> 01:39:20,351
<font face="Comic Sans MS">They've been planning it for months.
They want you to attack.</font>

855
01:39:21,600 --> 01:39:22,829
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Read the letter.</font>

856
01:39:43,560 --> 01:39:45,199
<font face="Comic Sans MS">- Major?
- Yes, sir?</font>

857
01:39:47,760 --> 01:39:48,989
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Stand them down.</font>

858
01:39:49,760 --> 01:39:51,240
<font face="Comic Sans MS">- Yes, sir.
- Call up the orderlies.</font>

859
01:39:51,320 --> 01:39:52,640
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Tend the wounded.</font>

860
01:39:52,720 --> 01:39:54,313
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Hold the line
in case they counter.</font>

861
01:39:54,400 --> 01:39:55,914
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Yes, sir!</font>

862
01:39:56,000 --> 01:39:58,390
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Stand down! Stand down!</font>

863
01:40:01,520 --> 01:40:04,752
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Stand down!</font>

864
01:40:04,840 --> 01:40:08,072
<font face="Comic Sans MS">- Cease fire! Cease fire!
- Stand down!</font>

865
01:40:12,040 --> 01:40:14,430
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I hoped today
might be a good day.</font>

866
01:40:16,760 --> 01:40:19,070
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Hope is a dangerous thing.</font>

867
01:40:21,240 --> 01:40:24,551
<font face="Comic Sans MS">That's it for now, and then next week
command will send a different message.</font>

868
01:40:25,560 --> 01:40:26,789
<font face="Comic Sans MS">"Attack at dawn."</font>

869
01:40:30,720 --> 01:40:32,712
<font face="Comic Sans MS">There is only one way this war ends.</font>

870
01:40:35,280 --> 01:40:37,078
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Last man standing.</font>

871
01:40:42,800 --> 01:40:44,393
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Have someone see to your wounds.</font>

872
01:40:47,520 --> 01:40:49,591
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Now, fuck off, Lance Corporal.</font>

873
01:40:55,480 --> 01:40:58,757
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Bearers! Stretcher bearers!</font>

874
01:40:59,800 --> 01:41:02,918
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Bearers! Stretcher bearers!</font>

875
01:41:03,600 --> 01:41:04,795
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Well done, lad.</font>

876
01:41:06,000 --> 01:41:07,150
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Thank you, sir.</font>

877
01:41:09,600 --> 01:41:11,512
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Do you know where
Lieutenant Blake is, sir?</font>

878
01:41:12,080 --> 01:41:13,594
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Blake?</font>

879
01:41:13,680 --> 01:41:15,512
<font face="Comic Sans MS">There were two of us.</font>

880
01:41:15,600 --> 01:41:17,876
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I was sent here with his brother.</font>

881
01:41:17,960 --> 01:41:19,076
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Ah.</font>

882
01:41:20,160 --> 01:41:23,710
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Well, knowing Lieutenant Blake,
he would have gone over with his men.</font>

883
01:41:23,800 --> 01:41:25,314
<font face="Comic Sans MS">He was in the first wave.</font>

884
01:41:26,960 --> 01:41:28,838
<font face="Comic Sans MS">How could I find him, sir?</font>

885
01:41:28,920 --> 01:41:32,152
<font face="Comic Sans MS">You can try the casualty clearing station
behind the line.</font>

886
01:41:33,800 --> 01:41:34,995
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Otherwise...</font>

887
01:41:38,480 --> 01:41:39,630
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Thank you, sir.</font>

888
01:41:40,520 --> 01:41:41,840
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Major Hepburn, sir!</font>

889
01:42:33,280 --> 01:42:36,273
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Just keep movin'.
Keep movin', keep movin'.</font>

890
01:43:01,440 --> 01:43:04,751
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Sergeant, I have to find Lieutenant Blake.
Do you know where he is?</font>

891
01:43:04,840 --> 01:43:05,840
<font face="Comic Sans MS">No.</font>

892
01:43:26,040 --> 01:43:27,156
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Clear the way.</font>

893
01:43:27,760 --> 01:43:31,197
<font face="Comic Sans MS">- Sir, is Lieutenant Blake here?
- No idea.</font>

894
01:43:32,680 --> 01:43:33,830
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Move along, Corporal.</font>

895
01:43:35,400 --> 01:43:37,517
<font face="Comic Sans MS">If you can walk, move to the triage area.</font>

896
01:43:39,680 --> 01:43:42,639
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Help me!</font>

897
01:43:45,400 --> 01:43:46,516
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Lieutenant Blake!</font>

898
01:43:50,000 --> 01:43:53,357
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Sir, he's out.</font>

899
01:43:56,000 --> 01:43:57,514
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Out of the bloody way!</font>

900
01:43:58,920 --> 01:44:00,149
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Blake?</font>

901
01:44:02,760 --> 01:44:04,877
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Has anyone seen Lieutenant Blake?</font>

902
01:44:06,760 --> 01:44:09,719
<font face="Comic Sans MS">He's hemorrhaging.
Go quickly. He needs a surgeon.</font>

903
01:44:16,520 --> 01:44:18,557
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Amputation. Straight to surgery.</font>

904
01:44:23,400 --> 01:44:24,550
<font face="Comic Sans MS">My leg!</font>

905
01:44:27,680 --> 01:44:29,399
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I need some help here! Quickly!</font>

906
01:44:34,240 --> 01:44:36,311
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I need something now!</font>

907
01:44:40,160 --> 01:44:41,560
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Coming through!</font>

908
01:44:55,440 --> 01:44:57,272
<font face="Comic Sans MS">All right, come on, boys.</font>

909
01:44:57,360 --> 01:45:00,273
<font face="Comic Sans MS">He's taken one in the leg.
He's lost a lot of blood.</font>

910
01:45:00,360 --> 01:45:01,360
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Sir.</font>

911
01:45:01,361 --> 01:45:03,477
<font face="Comic Sans MS">- Lieutenant Blake?
- Yes?</font>

912
01:45:05,360 --> 01:45:06,919
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Do you need medical assistance?</font>

913
01:45:08,520 --> 01:45:11,513
<font face="Comic Sans MS">No, sir. I'm from the 8th.</font>

914
01:45:11,600 --> 01:45:13,273
<font face="Comic Sans MS">What the hell are you doing here?</font>

915
01:45:14,240 --> 01:45:17,119
<font face="Comic Sans MS">- I was sent here to deliver a message.
- The 8th?</font>

916
01:45:17,200 --> 01:45:18,554
<font face="Comic Sans MS">You must know my brother.</font>

917
01:45:19,880 --> 01:45:22,918
<font face="Comic Sans MS">- I was sent here with him.
- Tom's here? Where is he?</font>

918
01:45:29,560 --> 01:45:30,960
<font face="Comic Sans MS">It was very quick.</font>

919
01:45:33,560 --> 01:45:34,789
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I'm sorry.</font>

920
01:45:58,920 --> 01:46:00,115
<font face="Comic Sans MS">What's your name?</font>

921
01:46:01,280 --> 01:46:02,396
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Schofield, sir.</font>

922
01:46:05,880 --> 01:46:07,109
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Sorry, what?</font>

923
01:46:07,920 --> 01:46:09,673
<font face="Comic Sans MS">It's Schofield, sir.</font>

924
01:46:09,800 --> 01:46:10,995
<font face="Comic Sans MS">William Schofield.</font>

925
01:46:12,360 --> 01:46:13,430
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Will.</font>

926
01:46:15,880 --> 01:46:18,998
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Well, you need some food.
Get yourself to the mess tent.</font>

927
01:46:34,000 --> 01:46:35,000
<font face="Comic Sans MS">If I may...</font>

928
01:46:36,080 --> 01:46:37,753
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I'd like to write to your mother.</font>

929
01:46:38,840 --> 01:46:40,832
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Tell her that Tom wasn't alone.</font>

930
01:46:44,400 --> 01:46:45,400
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Of course.</font>

931
01:46:48,240 --> 01:46:49,240
<font face="Comic Sans MS">He was...</font>

932
01:46:51,200 --> 01:46:52,520
<font face="Comic Sans MS">He was a good man.</font>

933
01:46:54,760 --> 01:46:56,319
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Always telling funny stories.</font>

934
01:46:59,480 --> 01:47:00,834
<font face="Comic Sans MS">He saved my life.</font>

935
01:47:05,000 --> 01:47:06,992
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I am glad you were with him.</font>

936
01:47:13,280 --> 01:47:14,396
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Thank you, Will.</font>

